  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I recovery whatsapp messagess?",
  "response": "Recovering WhatsApp messages depends on whether you have a backup or not. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you restore your WhatsApp messages:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Restore from a Backup (If Available)**\n\n#### **For Android:**\n1. **Uninstall and Reinstall WhatsApp**:  \n   - Uninstall WhatsApp from your phone.  \n   - Reinstall it from the Google Play Store.  \n\n2. **Verify Your Phone Number**:  \n   - Open WhatsApp and verify your phone number.  \n\n3. **Restore Backup**:  \n   - When prompted, tap **Restore** to recover your messages and media from Google Drive or local storage.  \n\n4. **Complete Setup**:  \n   - Wait for the restoration process to complete, then tap **Next**.  \n\n#### **For iPhone:**\n1. **Uninstall and Reinstall WhatsApp**:  \n   - Delete WhatsApp from your iPhone.  \n   - Reinstall it from the App Store.  \n\n2. **Verify Your Phone Number**:  \n   - Open WhatsApp and verify your phone number.  \n\n3. **Restore Backup**:  \n   - When prompted, tap **Restore Chat History** to recover your messages and media from iCloud.  \n\n4. **Complete Setup**:  \n   - Wait for the restoration process to complete, then tap **Next**.  \n\n---\n\n### **2. Restore Without a Backup**\n\nIf you don\u2019t have a backup, your options are limited, but you can try the following:\n\n#### **Check Local Files (Android Only)**\n   - WhatsApp stores local backups on Android devices. Go to **Internal Storage > WhatsApp > Databases** and look for a file named `msgstore.db.crypt12`. This is your local backup.  \n   - Rename the file to `msgstore.db.crypt12` (if it has a different name) and follow the steps in **Restore from a Backup** above.  \n\n#### **Use Third-Party Tools (Proceed with Caution)**\n   - There are third-party software tools (e.g., Dr.Fone, iMobie, etc.) that claim to recover deleted WhatsApp messages. These tools may work if the data hasn\u2019t been overwritten.  \n   - Always use trusted and verified software to avoid data breaches or malware.  \n\n---\n\n### **3. Ensure Backups Are Enabled for the Future**\nTo avoid losing messages in the future, make sure backups are enabled:\n\n#### **For Android**:  \n   - Open WhatsApp > **Settings** > **Chats** > **Chat Backup** > Tap **Back Up**.  \n\n#### **For iPhone**:  \n   - Open WhatsApp > **Settings** > **Chats** > **Chat Backup** > Tap **Back Up Now**.  \n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes**:\n- WhatsApp backups are tied to the phone number and device. You cannot restore a backup from one phone number to another.\n- If you switch between Android and iPhone, WhatsApp does not support cross-platform backup restoration.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
